{ Hello and welcome to Trample the French: French Tarrasch Variation!  Before we dive into the course, please allow me to say hello and briefly introduce myself. I am International Master Patrick Gong, and I am excited to introduce my very first Chessable course!  My chess journey began at the age of 10  (a bit later than many of my peers)  , and I've proudly represented Australia as a junior on the international stage. A highlight of my chess career was finishing equal 1st in the 2023 Oceania Chess Championship, where I also earned my IM title.  Nowadays, I am moving slightly beyond the chessboard  (and Earth!?)  , pursuing a PhD in astrobiology, focusing on engineering plant functions in space for extended missions to Mars and beyond.  I've always had mixed feelings about the French Defense. It was one of the first openings I played as a junior with the black pieces. Yet, as White, I've enjoyed significant success against it! The French Tarrasch has been a lifelong weapon of mine, in which I scored an impressive 83.3% win rate across 30+ over-the-board games, not too bad I suppose!  Therefore, it is my intention in this course to share some of the insights and strategies that have shaped my play. This endeavor wouldn't be possible without the encouragement from my long-time friend CM Adam Kelly, who suggested I write this course in the first place. I need to also thank my mother, Shirley, for her unwavering support.  Balancing this project with my PhD studies hasn't been easy, but it has been a fun ride. With this being my first Chessable course, I'm eager to hear your thoughts and suggestions, as they are invaluable for my improvement. I hope you find this course both enlightening and enjoyable.  Good luck, and let's dive into the course! }
