8... b5 9. dxc5 b4 10. a3 b3
{ Essentially, Black's only move since either pawn captures will be met with b4.   After  10...bxc3  11.b4  Qc7  12.Bb5  , White had an overwhelming advantage in Gong-Slater-Jones, Canberra 2015. Recalling that game certainly brings back sweet memories. }
11. Nd2
{ 11.Qxb3  Bxc5  12.Bxc5  Qxc5  is less than ideal. Black's queen is ready to  infiltrate via e3. }
11... Nxc5 12. Nxb3 Nxb3 13. Qxb3 Rb8
{ 13...d4  can be met with  14.Qb5!  , when White comes up two pawns ahead. }
14. Qa2 d4 15. b4
{ White consolidates the extra material and can look to finish off development. }
