Nxd4  Qc3+  , forking the bishop and rook. The author himself may have learned this nasty tactic the hard way...  11...Nb6  12.Bd3  cxd4  13.cxd4  a4  14.Ne2  . @@StartBracket@@After  14.b4  Bd7  ,  preparing ...Na7 and ...Bb5, Black's position looks alright as well.  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/1pq1bppp/1nn1p3/3pP3/p2P1P1P/PP1B1N2/4N1P1/1RBQK2R b Kkq - 1 14@@EndFEN@@  14...axb3  15.Rxb3  Nc4  16.O-O  g6  and  with the pawns on e6 and g6 firmly stopping White from playing f4-f5, Black finds good counterplay against White's queenside structure without exposing their king to danger. }
8... Be7 9. h5 { White gains more space on the kingside. } 9... f6 10. Bd3
{ The bishop can now be developed thanks to Black's ...f7-f6, a move that exposes Black's king to a check on g6. }
10... cxd4 11. cxd4 fxe5
{ 11...Nxd4  may first appear to win a pawn, but after  12.Nxd4  Qxd4  13.Bg6+  , it is actually Black who must part with the queen. This is a rather common tactic in the French so definitely one to remember! }
12. fxe5 O-O 13. Bc2
{ White threatens the dangerous Qd1-d3-h7. Note that with the pawn already on h5, Black can't play ...g7-g6 to protect the key light squares. }
13... Bb4+ 14. Ke2
{ 14.Bd2  would allow Black to respond with  14...Nxd4  , when White's powerful center collapses. }
14... Ncxe5
{ Without this sacrifice, it is hard to believe that Black can deal with the threat Qd1-d3-h7. Here Black at least tries to target the White's king still in the center. }
15. dxe5 Nxe5 16. Be3
{ 16.Nxe5??  would be absolutely disastrous. After  16...Qf2+  17.Kd3  b6  , the threat  of ...Ba6+ is deadly and the engine announces White's doom with a checkmate in 6. }
16... Qa6+ 17. Bd3
{ Even without the pawns around, White's king can still be relatively safe behind the minor pieces. Black might have a pair of bishops and two pawns for a knight, but White can try and blockade the central pawns with a timely Be3-d4-e5.   For example,  17...Nxd3  18.Qxd3  b6  19.Bd4!  Qxd3+  20.Kxd3  Ba6+  21.Ke3  Bd6  22.Be5  and White can look to convert the extra material. }
*

