{ With a simultaneous attack on White's rook and bishop, Black will at least secure the bishop pair as compensation for White's active play. }
14. Ra1 Nxd3 15. Rxd3 Be7 16. Nfxd4
{ By capturing the d4-pawn with the knight on f3, we ensure our other knight can occupy a5, where it will attack the b7-bishop and put pressure on the a6-pawn. }
16... O-O 17. Nf5
{ Thanks to the discovered attack, we eliminate Black's prized bishop pair and continue focusing on the vulnerable a6-pawn.   After  17...Qe8  18.Nxe7+  Qxe7  19.Na5  Be4  20.Rda3  Rac8  21.c3  , we have excellent prospects by targeting Black's weakness  on a6. }
