15... Bd7
{ One of the few moves from Black that doesn't lose outright.   15...b5  allows the stylish finish  16.Nxb5!  axb5  17.Bxf6  gxf6  18.Qxh7#  . It highlights the danger Black faces with  White's b3+Bb2 setup.   Meanwhile  15...e5  , attacking the  queen on h3 with the c8-bishop is met with  16.Nf5  , when the knight coupled with  an incoming Qh4/g3 creates a rather dangerous attack on Black's king. }
16. Rae1
{ Sadly,  16.Nb5  no longer works due to  16...Bxb5!  , when after  17.Bxf6  Bxd3  , White parts  with the d3-bishop that was critical for the mating attack.   With  16.Rae1  , we are considering the idea of a  rook lift Re1-e3, when coupled with Qh4 and Rh3 could do some serious damage. }
16... Rfe8 17. Qh4
