Bxd3 18. Qxd3 Ng4
{ Threatening a mate-in-1, which we aren't going to fall for! } 19. h4
{ We're not scared of ghosts, and with  19.h4  , we put an end to Black’s kingside attack. Now it's Black who must be cautious about overextending. Neither  19...Bxh4  20.gxh4  Qxh4  21.Qg3  nor @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/p3bppp/Pp2p2q/8/3N2nP/1P1Q2P1/1BP2P2/R4RK1 b - h3 0 19@@EndFEN@@  19...g5  20.Qe2  Qh5  21.Nc6  Rae8  22.Ra4  works in Black's favor. We can refocus our attention on exploiting the  weak a7-pawn. }
