4. c3
{ The most suitable move to fit our overall repertoire. While the engine prefers  4.Ngf3  , Black can now play  4...Nf6  , when  5.e5  Nfd7  is pleasant but falls outside our repertoire  with the d4-e5-f4 center. Why make life intentionally harder for ourselves? }
4... Be7
{ 4...Nf6  5.e5  Nfd7  6.f4  gives White an extra move from @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/3PP3/8/PPPN1PPP/R1BQKBNR b KQkq - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Nf6  , and if Black tries @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp3ppp/2p1p3/3p4/3PP3/2P5/PP1N1PPP/R1BQKBNR b KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4...c5  , they are basically admitting that @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/3PP3/8/PPPN1PPP/R1BQKBNR b KQkq - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3...c6  was a mouse slip. }
5. Bd3 Qc7
