[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "6) Other 3rd Moves"]
[Black "Other 3rd Moves − 3...Be7 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 Be7
{ A waiting move. Black simply develops the bishop and waits for White to show their hands. }
4. c3 c5 5. dxc5
{ Trying to gain a tempo by exploiting Black's early bishop move. } 5... a5
{ A rare but reasonable move; ...a5 delays the capture of the c5-pawn, forcing us to reveal our plan. It also discourages b4 while introducing the idea of capturing the c5 pawn with ...Na6xc5. }
6. Bb5+
{ However, the downside of ...a5 is the weakened b5-square, which we can immediately exploit. }
6... Bd7 7. a4 Bxc5
{ Further delaying the capture on c5 will make recovering the pawn even harder. After  7...Na6  8.Bxa6  Rxa6  9.exd5  exd5  10.Nb3  , we are poised to protect  the c5-pawn with Be3, making it difficult for Black to reclaim it. }
8. exd5 Bxb5
