5... c5 6. Ndf3 Nc6 7. c3 cxd4 8. cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Kf2 f6 10. g3
{ As we mentioned in the repertoire, it is important to enable White's king to sidestep any potential headaches following the opening of the f-file. }
10... fxe5 11. fxe5 O-O 12. Kg2
