1... e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 c5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Ngf3 cxd4 6. Bc4 Qd6 7. O-O Nf6 8.
Nb3 Nc6 9. Nbxd4 Nxd4 10. Nxd4 a6 11. b3 { Our repertoire recommendation. }
11... Be7 12. Bb2 O-O 13. Qf3 Qc7 14. Rfe1 b5 15. Bd3 Bb7 16. Qh3
{ White has a very dangerous attack, and even a grandmaster of Korchnoi's caliber did not find Black's best defense. }
16... Bc8
